13/09/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski met with his Montenegrin counterpart, Filip Vujanovic, in Skopje on Wednesday (September 12th). 
They exchanged views about the countries' EU and NATO membership aspirations, and discussed boosting economic co-operation, including through the establishment of a joint business council.
Vujanovic also met with Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski and Parliament Speaker Ljubisa Georgievski. 
After the meeting, Gruevski and Vujanovic said relations between Macedonia and Montenegro are "historically friendly" and the two countries should deepen bilateral co-operation, both on a regional and a European level. 
(MIA, A1, RTCG, Makfax - 12/09/07)
